# project

- label: runtime is Bun
  command: grep -q 'lockfileVersion' bun.lock
- label: TUI dashboard for skill usage stats across AI coding tools
  command: grep -q 'skill usage stats' package.json
- label: written in TypeScript with strict mode enabled
  command: grep -q '"strict": true' tsconfig.json
- label: ES module project (type: module)
  command: grep -q '"type": "module"' package.json
- label: uses for TUI rendering
  command: grep -q '@opentui/core' package.json
  tags: [opentui/core]
- label: entry point is src/main.ts, exposed as 'skilled' bin command
  command: test -f src/main.ts && grep -q '"skilled"' package.json
- label: no build step — runs directly via bun (noEmit: true in tsconfig)
  command: grep -q '"noEmit": true' tsconfig.json
- no test suite
- label: only runtime dependency is
  command: jq -e '.dependencies | keys == ["@opentui/core"]' package.json >/dev/null
  tags: [opentui/core]

# architecture
- label: provider pattern: providers implement Provider interface (name, available, collect)
  command: grep -q 'interface Provider' src/providers/base.ts
- label: single provider: ClaudeCodeProvider reads ~/.claude/history.jsonl
  command: grep -q 'ClaudeCodeProvider' src/providers/claude-code.ts
- label: app.ts run() accepts Provider[] and renders the full TUI
  command: grep -q 'providers: Provider\[\]' src/app.ts
- data flow: Provider.collect() → aggregation (data.ts) → TUI (app.ts)

# data
- label: three core types: SkillCall, SkillCount, DayCount (defined in models.ts)
  command: grep -q 'SkillCall' src/models.ts && grep -q 'SkillCount' src/models.ts && grep -q 'DayCount' src/models.ts
- label: SkillCall captures: skill, timestamp, project, sessionId, source
  command: grep -q 'sessionId' src/models.ts && grep -q 'source: string' src/models.ts
- label: aggregation functions: skillCounts, dailyCounts, weeklyCounts (data.ts)
  command: grep -q 'export function skillCounts' src/data.ts && grep -q 'export function dailyCounts' src/data.ts && grep -q 'export function weeklyCounts' src/data.ts

# provider

## claude-code
- label: skill names extracted from display field via regex /^\/([a-zA-Z][a-zA-Z0-9_-]*)$/
  command: grep -q 'a-zA-Z.*a-zA-Z0-9_' src/providers/claude-code.ts
- label: builtin commands (clear, model, usage, help, etc.) are filtered out
  command: grep -q 'BUILTINS' src/providers/claude-code.ts
- label: malformed JSON lines in history are silently skipped
  command: grep -q 'catch' src/providers/claude-code.ts

# ui
- full-screen TUI: header, stats row, left/right panels, footer
- label: header renders animated Perlin noise background with blocky pixel font
  command: grep -q 'fbm' src/app.ts && grep -q 'PIXEL_FONT' src/app.ts
- label: stats cards show: CALLS, SKILLS, PROJECTS, SOURCES
  command: grep -q 'CALLS' src/app.ts && grep -q 'SKILLS' src/app.ts && grep -q 'PROJECTS' src/app.ts && grep -q 'SOURCES' src/app.ts
- left panel: skill frequency bar chart + weekly sparkline
- label: right panel: 16-week activity heatmap + recent activity log
  command: grep -q 'WEEKS.*=.*16' src/app.ts
- label: staggered animations on bars, sparkline, and heatmap cells
  command: grep -q 'barStagger' src/app.ts && grep -q 'outBack' src/app.ts
- label: Perlin noise implementation with fractional Brownian motion (fbm) in noise.ts
  command: grep -q 'export function fbm' src/noise.ts

## interaction
- label: three sort modes: by count, alphabetical, recent (cycled with 's')
  command: grep -q 'count.*alpha.*recent\|sortMode' src/app.ts
- keyboard: q/esc quit, r refresh, s sort, j/k scroll, g/G top/bottom, ctrl+d/u page

## theme
- label: GitHub-inspired dark mode theme with 14-color bar palette and 5-level green heatmap
  command: test -f src/theme.ts

# ui > interaction
- tab key toggles sort direction between ascending and descending @implemented
- bar chart bottom title shows ▲/▼ indicator next to sort mode label @implemented

# ui > analytics
- enter key on bar chart opens skill detail panel replacing right column @implemented
- skill detail panel shows per-project usage breakdown, session count, first/last used dates, and weekly usage sparkline @implemented
- 'a' key toggles audit view replacing main layout with library health insights @implemented
- audit view shows: stale skills (unused 30+ days), one-off skills (used once), declining skills (usage dropped 50%+ over last 4 weeks vs prior 4) @implemented
